<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>HTML Link Tags Example</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial;
            background: #f4f4f4;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
        }

        .box {
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 15px auto;
            width: 60%;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px gray;
        }

        a {
            display: block;
            margin: 10px;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: blue;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

<h1>HTML Link Tag Demonstration</h1>

<div class="box">
    <h3>1. Basic Link</h3>
    <a href="https://www.google.com">Go to Google</a>
</div>

<div class="box">
    <h3>2. Open Link in New Tab</h3>
    <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org" target="_blank">Open Wikipedia</a>
</div>

<div class="box">
    <h3>3. Link to Another Page</h3>
    <a href="index.html">Go to Home Page</a>
</div>

<div class="box">
    <h3>4. Email Link</h3>
    <a href="mailto:example@gmail.com">Send Email</a>
</div>

<div class="box">
    <h3>5. Image as Link</h3>
    <a href="https://www.github.com" target="_blank">
        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/150" alt="GitHub Link">
    </a>
</div>

<div class="box">
    <h3>6. Internal Page Link (Bookmark)</h3>
    <a href="#section">Go to Section Below</a>
</div>

<div class="box" id="section">
    <h3>This is Target Section</h3>
    <p>You jumped here using internal link.</p>
</div>

</body>
</html>
